不知道从哪里开始，

26
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:21,800
or they're overconfident, taking AI outputs at face value,
要么他们过于自信，直接接受AI的输出，

27
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:23,760
not knowing what to question,
不知道该质疑什么，

28
00:01:23,760 --> 00:01:27,000
producing work that looks right, but isn't.
产生看起来正确但实际上不对的作品。

29
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,760
Both patterns lead to the same place.
这两种模式都导致同样的结果。

30
00:01:29,760 --> 00:01:33,599
Mediocre results and enormous missed potential.
平庸的结果和巨大的潜在机会被错失。

31
00:01:33,599 --> 00:01:35,319
There is a third way.
There is a third way.

32
00:01:36,379 --> 00:01:38,239
That third way has a name,
That third way has a name,

33
00:01:38,239 --> 00:01:41,339
and it was developed by some of the world's leading thinkers
and it was developed by some of the world's leading thinkers

34
00:01:41,339 --> 00:01:43,819
on human AI interaction.
on human AI interaction.

35
00:01:43,819 --> 00:01:45,519
It's called AI fluency.
It's called AI fluency.

36
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:48,919
Anthropica partner with Professor Joseph Faller
Anthropica partner with Professor Joseph Faller

37
00:01:48,919 --> 00:01:50,360
from University College Cork
from University College Cork

38
00:01:50,360 --> 00:01:52,919
and Professor Rick Dutkin from Ringling College
and Professor Rick Dutkin from Ringling College

39
00:01:52,959 --> 00:01:55,639
to create a rigorous, accessible framework
to create a rigorous, accessible framework

40
00:01:55,639 --> 00:01:57,980
for working with AI well.
for working with AI well.

41
00:01:57,980 --> 00:02:00,080
They define AI fluency as the ability
They define AI fluency as the ability

42
00:02:00,080 --> 00:02:04,239
to work with AI systems in ways that are effective,
to work with AI systems in ways that are effective,

43
00:02:04,239 --> 00:02:08,000
efficient, ethical, and safe.
efficient, ethical, and safe.

44
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:11,160
Four words, but they represent a completely different
Four words, but they represent a completely different

45
00:02:11,160 --> 00:02:14,179
relationship with AI than most people have today.
relationship with AI than most people have today.

46
00:02:15,039 --> 00:02:17,520
Here's what I found most compelling
Here's what I found most compelling

47
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:21,080
about Anthropica's approach to AI education.
about Anthropica's approach to AI education.

48
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:22,759
Their team has said,
Their team has said,

49
00:02:22,759 --> 00:02:26,360
we would much rather teach a million people not to use AI
we would much rather teach a million people not to use AI

50
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,679
than watch a billion people
than watch a billion people

51
00:02:27,679 --> 00:02:30,839
become dependent on this technology.
become dependent on this technology.

52
00:02:30,839 --> 00:02:31,919
Read that again.
Read that again.

53
00:02:31,919 --> 00:02:34,339
This isn't about using AI more.
This isn't about using AI more.

54
00:02:34,339 --> 00:02:38,119
It's about using it with intention on your terms
It's about using it with intention on your terms

55
00:02:38,119 --> 00:02:41,600
as a genuine thinker partner, not as a crutch.
as a genuine thinker partner, not as a crutch.

56
00:02:42,919 --> 00:02:47,199
The success criterion for AI fluency is beautifully simple.
The success criterion for AI fluency is beautifully simple.

57
00:02:47,199 --> 00:02:50,320
Can you clearly articulate when you want to use the AI
Can you clearly articulate when you want to use the AI

58
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:52,160
and when you don't?
and when you don't?

59
00:02:52,160 --> 00:02:54,080
Not how many prompts you know,
Not how many prompts you know,

60
00:02:54,080 --> 00:02:57,559
not how many tools you've tried, just that.
not how many tools you've tried, just that.

61
00:02:57,559 --> 00:03:01,179
The ability to make a conscious, intentional choice.
有意识、故意选择的能力。

62
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:04,759
So how do you build that capacity?
那么你如何建立这种能力？

63
00:03:04,759 --> 00:03:06,880
Through the AI fluency frameworks,
通过AI流畅性框架，

64
00:03:06,880 --> 00:03:09,479
a set of four interconnected competencies
一套四个相互关联的能力

65
00:03:09,479 --> 00:03:13,080
known as the four Ds, delegation, description,
称为四个D：委派、描述、

66
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:15,960
discernment, and diligence.
辨别和勤奋。

67
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:18,139
Let's go through each one.
让我们逐一了解。

68
00:03:18,139 --> 00:03:20,699
The first D is delegation.
第一个D是委派。

69
00:03:20,699 --> 00:03:23,940
Delegation asks one fundamental question.
委派提出一个基本问题。

70
00:03:23,940 --> 00:03:25,899
Who does what?
谁做什么？

71
00:03:25,899 --> 00:03:28,179
In every interaction with AI,
在与AI的每次互动中，

72
00:03:28,179 --> 00:03:31,699
you are making choice consciously or not
你都在有意识或无意识地做出选择，

73
00:03:31,699 --> 00:03:35,300
about what role AI plays and what role you play.
关于AI扮演什么角色以及你扮演什么角色。

74
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:38,520
AI fluency means making that choice deliberately.
AI流畅性意味着故意做出这个选择。

75
00:03:39,660 --> 00:03:41,580
There are three parts to delegation.
委派有三个部分。

76
00:03:41,580 --> 00:03:43,860
The first one is go clarity.
第一部分是明确目标。

77
00:03:43,860 --> 00:03:46,380
Before you open any AI tool,
在打开任何AI工具之前，

78
00:03:46,380 --> 00:03:49,539
know what you're actually trying to achieve.
要知道你实际上想要实现什么。

79
00:03:49,539 --> 00:03:52,020
Help me write an email is not a go.
“帮我写一封邮件”并不是一个明确的目标。

80
00:03:52,020 --> 00:03:54,259
Draft a follow-up email to client
给客户起草一封跟进邮件，

81
00:03:54,259 --> 00:03:56,619
who went silent after our proposal.
他在我们的提案后沉默不语。

82
00:03:56,619 --> 00:03:59,820
Acknowledge the delay, briefly restate the value,
承认延迟，简要重申价值，

83
00:03:59,820 --> 00:04:02,619
and end with a single low friction ask.
并以一个简单的低阻力请求结束。

84
00:04:02,619 --> 00:04:03,839
That's a go.
这才是明确的目标。

85
00:04:04,779 --> 00:04:07,259
The second is platform awareness.
第二部分是平台意识。

86
00:04:07,259 --> 00:04:09,399
Different tools have different strengths.
不同的工具有不同的优势。

87
00:04:09,399 --> 00:04:13,380
Claude is particularly strong at structural analysis,
Claude在结构分析、

88
00:04:13,380 --> 00:04:16,339
nuanced writing, and complex reasoning.
细致写作和复杂推理方面特别强。

89
00:04:17,179 --> 00:04:19,260
Knowing where to go for what kind of work
知道在什么工作中该使用什么工具，

90
00:04:19,260 --> 00:04:20,839
is itself a skill.
本身就是一种技能。

91
00:04:21,980 --> 00:04:24,739
And the last one, task distribution.
And the last one, task distribution.

92
00:04:24,739 --> 00:04:27,940
AI handles execution and pattern work.
AI handles execution and pattern work.

93
00:04:27,940 --> 00:04:30,500
You handle direction, judgment,
You handle direction, judgment,

94
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:32,739
and relationship-sensitive decisions.
and relationship-sensitive decisions.

95
00:04:33,980 --> 00:04:35,899
The second D is description,
The second D is description,

96
00:04:35,899 --> 00:04:38,260
how you communicate with AI.
how you communicate with AI.

97
00:04:38,260 --> 00:04:40,260
This is where most people struggle,
This is where most people struggle,

98
00:04:40,260 --> 00:04:43,540
which is exactly why they get mediocre results.
which is exactly why they get mediocre results.

99
00:04:43,540 --> 00:04:45,760
Here's the golden rule.
Here's the golden rule.

100
00:04:45,799 --> 00:04:50,119
Vague input always produces vague output.
Vague input always produces vague output.

101
00:04:50,119 --> 00:04:53,339
Great description uses what's called the three Ps.
Great description uses what's called the three Ps.

102
00:04:54,779 --> 00:04:57,640
The first P is product description.
The first P is product description.

103
00:04:57,640 --> 00:05:00,079
Tell AI exactly what you want,
Tell AI exactly what you want,

104
00:05:00,079 --> 00:05:03,059
not just the topic, the format, the audience,
not just the topic, the format, the audience,

105
00:05:03,059 --> 00:05:05,959
the tone, the length, be specific.
the tone, the length, be specific.

106
00:05:05,959 --> 00:05:08,679
The second P is process description.
The second P is process description.

107
00:05:08,679 --> 00:05:11,040
Tell AI how to approach the task.
Tell AI how to approach the task.

108
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:13,040
Should it analyze multiple angles
Should it analyze multiple angles

109
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:15,559
or break the work into stages?
or break the work into stages?

110
00:05:16,359 --> 00:05:18,760
The third P is performance description.
The third P is performance description.

111
00:05:18,760 --> 00:05:21,799
Set expectations for the interaction itself.
Set expectations for the interaction itself.

112
00:05:21,799 --> 00:05:24,720
Should AI ask clarifying questions,
Should AI ask clarifying questions,

113
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:26,519
challenging your assumptions?
challenging your assumptions?

114
00:05:26,519 --> 00:05:28,559
Be brief or thorough.
Be brief or thorough.

115
00:05:28,559 --> 00:05:31,200
Think of it as briefing a brilliant new colleague.
Think of it as briefing a brilliant new colleague.

116
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:34,160
The better your brief, the better their work.
The better your brief, the better their work.

117
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:35,559
I want to spend a moment on this
I want to spend a moment on this

118
00:05:35,559 --> 00:05:37,920
because it's one of the most important principles
because it's one of the most important principles

119
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:39,440
in AI fluency.
in AI fluency.

120
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:43,619
Vague input always produces vague output.
Vague input always produces vague output.

121
00:05:43,619 --> 00:05:45,040
Most AI frustration,
大多数对人工智能的挫败感，

122
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:47,100
the sense that AI doesn't really get it,
源于对人工智能理解的怀疑，

123
00:05:47,100 --> 00:05:48,739
traces back to this.
这可以追溯到这里。

124
00:05:48,739 --> 00:05:51,179
It's not a limitation of the model,
这不是模型的局限，

125
00:05:51,179 --> 00:05:53,440
it's a limitation of the description.
而是描述的局限。

126
00:05:54,619 --> 00:05:56,459
The third D is discernment,
第三个D是辨别力，

127
00:05:56,459 --> 00:05:59,480
and this is where AI fluency separates professionals
这就是人工智能流利度将专业人士

128
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:01,380
from casual users.
与普通用户区分开的地方。

129
00:06:01,380 --> 00:06:04,299
AI sounds confident even when it's wrong.
人工智能即使错误也听起来很自信。

130
00:06:04,299 --> 00:06:06,540
It states incorrect facts
它以与正确事实相同的语气

131
00:06:06,540 --> 00:06:09,179
with the same tone as correct ones.
陈述不正确的事实。

132
00:06:09,179 --> 00:06:11,260
It generates plausible sounding reasoning
它生成听起来合理的推理，

133
00:06:11,260 --> 00:06:13,339
that doesn't quite hold together.
但并不完全成立。

134
00:06:14,059 --> 00:06:17,820
The fourth P is trusting professional language.
第四个P是信任专业语言。

135
00:06:17,820 --> 00:06:21,019
Discernment is the practice of reading AI outputs
辨别力是对人工智能输出的

136
00:06:21,019 --> 00:06:24,019
with genuine critical evaluation.
真实批判性评估的实践。

137
00:06:24,019 --> 00:06:26,059
There are three lenses.
有三个视角。

138
00:06:26,059 --> 00:06:28,980
The first one is part of discernment.
第一个是辨别力的一部分。

139
00:06:28,980 --> 00:06:30,540
Is this accurate?
这准确吗？

140
00:06:30,540 --> 00:06:32,619
Is it logically coherent?
逻辑上连贯吗？

141
00:06:32,619 --> 00:06:35,019
Is it appropriate for my purpose?
适合我的目的吗？

142
00:06:35,019 --> 00:06:39,019
Do I have the domain knowledge to catch what might be wrong?
我是否拥有识别错误的领域知识？

143
00:06:39,019 --> 00:06:41,820
The second is processed discernment.
第二个是处理后的辨别力。

144
00:06:42,299 --> 00:06:43,859
Or just organizing information
或者只是将信息

145
00:06:43,859 --> 00:06:46,260
into impressive looking structures.
组织成看起来令人印象深刻的结构。

146
00:06:46,260 --> 00:06:48,459
Is that real thinking here?
这里是真正的思考吗？

147
00:06:48,459 --> 00:06:49,739
Or confident noise?
还是自信的噪音？

148
00:06:50,779 --> 00:06:53,500
Third one is performance discernment.
第三个是表现辨别力。

149
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:55,899
Did the response actually help me?
这个回应真的对我有帮助吗？

150
00:06:55,899 --> 00:06:58,220
Does it match the tone I needed?
它符合我需要的语气吗？

151
00:06:58,220 --> 00:07:00,700
Is it the right level of depth?
深度合适吗？

152
00:07:00,700 --> 00:07:02,459
Here's the habit to build.
这是要培养的习惯。

153
00:07:02,459 --> 00:07:06,100
Read every AI output as if a competitor wrote it.
把每个AI输出都当作竞争对手写的。

154
00:07:06,100 --> 00:07:08,899
Skeptically, not looking for what's right,
持怀疑态度，而不是寻找正确的，

155
00:07:08,899 --> 00:07:11,820
looking for what might be wrong.
寻找可能出错的地方。

156
00:07:11,820 --> 00:07:14,019
The fourth D is diligence.
第四个D是勤奋。

157
00:07:14,019 --> 00:07:17,540
And it comes down to one word, responsibility.
归结为一个词，责任。

158
00:07:17,540 --> 00:07:20,059
No matter how good the AI output is,
无论AI输出多么优秀，

159
00:07:20,059 --> 00:07:24,059
you are always responsible for what you put your name on.
你始终对自己署名的内容负责。

160
00:07:24,059 --> 00:07:25,380
There are three parts.
分为三个部分。

161
00:07:25,380 --> 00:07:28,299
The first part is creation diligence.
第一部分是创作勤奋。

162
00:07:28,299 --> 00:07:30,299
Choose your AI tools deliberately.
故意选择你的AI工具。

163
00:07:30,299 --> 00:07:32,980
If you're handling sensitive information,
如果你处理敏感信息，

164
00:07:32,980 --> 00:07:37,380
are you sure that platform has appropriate data policies?
你确定那个平台有适当的数据政策吗？

165
00:07:37,380 --> 00:07:39,779
The second is transparency diligence.
第二部分是透明度勤奋。

166
00:07:39,779 --> 00:07:43,179
When the AI has played a significant role in your work,
当AI在你的工作中发挥了重要作用时，

167
00:07:43,179 --> 00:07:45,059
be honest about that.
要诚实地说明这一点。

168
00:07:45,059 --> 00:07:47,579
The third is deployment diligence.
第三部分是部署勤奋。

169
00:07:47,579 --> 00:07:49,980
Before anything reaches another person,
在任何东西传递给其他人之前，

170
00:07:49,980 --> 00:07:52,540
a professor, a client, a colleague,
教授、客户、同事，

171
00:07:52,540 --> 00:07:54,940
it passes through your judgment.
都要经过你的判断。

172
00:07:54,940 --> 00:07:58,019
AI's first draft is now the final product.
AI的初稿现在是最终产品。

173
00:07:58,019 --> 00:08:00,540
You are the last line of quality control.
你是最后的质量控制线。

174
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:03,779
What's beautiful about this four D
这四个D的美妙之处在于，

175
00:08:03,779 --> 00:08:07,100
is that they form a cycle, not a checklist.
它们形成一个循环，而不是一个清单。

176
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:10,059
You delegate, you describe,
你委派，你描述，

177
00:08:10,059 --> 00:08:13,140
you discern, you practice diligence.
你辨别，你实践勤奋。

178
00:08:13,140 --> 00:08:16,899
Then you loop back, smart delegation next time,
然后你再回头，下次智能委派，

179
00:08:16,899 --> 00:08:20,500
sharper descriptions, more sophisticated discernment.
更精准的描述，更复杂的辨别。

180
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:24,540
This is what it means to grow as an AI-fluent practitioner,
这就是作为一个AI流利的从业者成长的意义。

181
00:08:24,540 --> 00:08:26,579
not just doing tasks.
不仅仅是执行任务。

182
00:08:26,579 --> 00:08:29,260
Let's bring this to life with a real example,
让我们用一个真实的例子来说明，

183
00:08:29,260 --> 00:08:33,059
one that shows AI fluency at its most creative.
一个展示AI创造力的流畅性。

184
00:08:33,059 --> 00:08:35,900
Imagine you're a writer collaborating with AI
想象你是一位与AI合作的作家，

185
00:08:35,940 --> 00:08:37,940
to create character concepts for a story.
为一个故事创作角色概念。

186
00:08:37,940 --> 00:08:41,500
You have a world, a plot, and a vision.
你有一个世界，一个情节和一个愿景。

187
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:44,580
Where does AI fit and where does it not?
AI适合什么，哪里又不适合？

188
00:08:44,580 --> 00:08:46,020
Pause and think about it.
停下来想一想。

189
00:08:46,940 --> 00:08:50,700
With delegation, you draw a deliberate line independently.
通过委托，你独立划定了一条明确的界限。

190
00:08:50,700 --> 00:08:54,500
You develop the character's core, their deepest desires,
你发展角色的核心，他们最深的渴望，

191
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:57,539
their defining flaws, their backstory.
他们的缺陷，他们的背景故事。

192
00:08:57,539 --> 00:08:59,219
These belong to you.
这些属于你。

193
00:08:59,219 --> 00:09:01,580
They are the soul of the character.
它们是角色的灵魂。

194
00:09:02,460 --> 00:09:05,979
Through AI collaboration, you explore personality,
通过与AI的合作，你探索个性，

195
00:09:05,979 --> 00:09:09,619
appearance, how this character fits the story world,
外貌，这个角色如何融入故事世界，

196
00:09:09,619 --> 00:09:14,500
and how they're engaged with others across later chapters.
以及他们在后面的章节中如何与他人互动。

197
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:17,340
The principle here is that humans define the soul
这里的原则是人类定义灵魂

198
00:09:17,340 --> 00:09:18,500
and the core.
和核心。

199
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:21,539
AI exhausts the possibilities of vision,
AI耗尽了视觉、

200
00:09:21,539 --> 00:09:23,659
detail, and collision.
细节和碰撞的可能性。

201
00:09:23,659 --> 00:09:27,419
With description, you give AI the full story background,
通过描述，你向AI提供完整的故事背景，

202
00:09:27,419 --> 00:09:31,059
the world's rules, its tensions, its history,
世界的规则、紧张关系、历史，

203
00:09:31,380 --> 00:09:34,140
you specify what kinds of character this story needs
你具体说明这个故事需要什么样的角色，

204
00:09:34,140 --> 00:09:36,260
and crucially, what it doesn't.
以及至关重要的，它不需要什么。

205
00:09:36,260 --> 00:09:40,099
So every suggestion stays inside your creative vision.
因此，每个建议都保持在你的创意愿景之内。

206
00:09:40,099 --> 00:09:42,619
You also establish cultural context,
你还建立文化背景，

207
00:09:42,619 --> 00:09:45,700
naming conventions, the aesthetic register,
命名惯例，审美风格，

208
00:09:45,700 --> 00:09:47,099
the emotional tone.
情感基调。

209
00:09:47,099 --> 00:09:49,179
With discernment, you keep elements
通过洞察力，你保留了

210
00:09:49,179 --> 00:09:51,460
that are essential to a key plot moment
对关键情节时刻至关重要的元素。

211
00:09:51,460 --> 00:09:54,900
or that sharply illuminate a character's personality.
或是能清晰照亮角色个性的。

212
00:09:54,900 --> 00:09:58,020
You modify whatever doesn't fit the world you've envisioned.
你修改任何不符合你设想的世界的东西。

213
00:09:58,020 --> 00:10:00,580
And here's the most powerful discernment practice,
这是最强大的辨别练习，

214
00:10:01,419 --> 00:10:04,659
deliberately discard AI's first two suggestions.
故意舍弃AI的前两个建议。

215
00:10:04,659 --> 00:10:07,380
They'll almost always be the most predictable.
它们几乎总是最可预测的。

216
00:10:07,380 --> 00:10:09,460
Go to the third or fourth idea.
去第三个或第四个想法。

217
00:10:09,460 --> 00:10:12,260
That's where the unexpected adjustment decision leaves.
那是意外调整决策的来源。

218
00:10:13,659 --> 00:10:16,739
With the diligence, every character that makes it
凭借努力，每个进入你故事的角色

219
00:10:16,739 --> 00:10:20,059
into your story is yours to stand behind.
都是你可以支持的。

220
00:10:20,059 --> 00:10:23,140
It can explain why they exist, what role they serve,
它可以解释他们为何存在，他们的角色，

221
00:10:23,140 --> 00:10:24,659
and how they were shaped.
以及他们是如何形成的。

222
00:10:24,659 --> 00:10:27,739
Hence, the most important thing I want you to take away.
因此，我希望你记住的最重要的事情。

223
00:10:27,739 --> 00:10:31,260
AI fluency is not about becoming more like a machine.
AI流利度并不是变得更像机器。

224
00:10:31,260 --> 00:10:33,940
It's about becoming more fully human.
而是变得更加人性化。

225
00:10:33,940 --> 00:10:35,780
When you're fluent with AI,
当你与AI流利时，

226
00:10:35,780 --> 00:10:38,419
your critical thinking doesn't diminish.
你的批判性思维不会减弱。

227
00:10:38,419 --> 00:10:39,500
It gets sharper
反而会更加敏锐，

228
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:42,059
because you have a powerful thinking partner.
因为你有一个强大的思维伙伴。

229
00:10:42,059 --> 00:10:44,260
Your judgment doesn't weaken.
你的判断力不会减弱。

230
00:10:44,260 --> 00:10:46,140
It gets more refined.
反而会更加精炼。

231
00:10:46,140 --> 00:10:48,460
Your creativity doesn't shrink.
你的创造力不会缩小。

232
00:10:48,460 --> 00:10:50,099
It expands.
反而会扩展。

233
00:10:50,099 --> 00:10:53,539
In a world where AI can generate endless content,
在一个AI可以生成无尽内容的世界里，

234
00:10:53,539 --> 00:10:56,299
your ability to think critically, to discern,
你批判性思考的能力、辨别能力、

235
00:10:56,299 --> 00:10:58,099
to take responsibility,
以及承担责任的能力，

236
00:10:58,099 --> 00:11:01,700
those are your most valuable assets.
这些都是你最宝贵的资产。

237
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:04,500
So here's what I'd encourage you to do.
所以这是我鼓励你做的。

238
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:08,460
First, take Anthropic's free AI fluency course.
首先，参加Anthropic的免费AI流利度课程。

239
00:11:08,460 --> 00:11:11,500
It's called AI Fluency Framework and Foundations.
它叫做AI流利度框架与基础。

240
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:15,299
It's free, it's rigorous, and it takes about an hour.
这是免费的，内容严谨，大约需要一个小时。

241
00:11:15,299 --> 00:11:16,700
I'll link it below.
我会把链接放在下面。

242
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:19,539
Second, the next time you work with AI,
第二，下次你使用AI时，

243
00:11:19,539 --> 00:11:21,780
go through the four Ds consciously.
要有意识地经历四个D。

244
00:11:21,780 --> 00:11:25,299
Delegate intentionally, describe precisely,
有意委派，准确描述，

245
00:11:25,299 --> 00:11:28,580
discern critically, and practice diligence.
批判性辨别，勤奋实践。

246
00:11:29,460 --> 00:11:32,219
Third, share this with someone who needs to hear it
第三，把这个分享给需要听的人，

247
00:11:32,219 --> 00:11:34,619
because AI fluency is a superpower
因为AI流利是一种超能力，

248
00:11:34,619 --> 00:11:37,780
and it's one that everyone deserves access to.
每个人都应该拥有这种能力。

249
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:40,780
Remember, you're not just here to use AI.
记住，你不仅仅是来使用AI的。

250
00:11:40,780 --> 00:11:43,140
You're here to work with it on your term.
你是来按照自己的方式与之合作的。
